# Security Best Practices

## Avoid 777 Permissions

Bad:

```bash
chmod 777 file.txt
```

---

## Use Least Privilege Principle

Give only necessary permissions.

---

## Secure Sensitive Files

Example:

```bash
chmod 600 credentials.txt
```

---

## Monitor SUID Files

Misconfigured SUID binaries can become privilege escalation vectors.

---

# Why Permissions Matter in Cybersecurity

Weak permissions may lead to:

* privilege escalation
* credential theft
* malicious code execution
* file tampering
* web shell uploads
* unauthorized access

Linux permissions are one of the most commonly checked areas during:

* VAPT
* system audits
* penetration testing
* privilege escalation assessments

